||TND098071061||[[Smokey Mountain Smelters]]||[[Knox County, Tennessee|Knox]]|| The site contains an abandoned [[aluminum]] smelter and a former [[fertilizer]] manufacturing plant.  Around 2,700 cubic yards of aluminum [[dross]], contain [[heavy metal (chemistry)|heavy metal]]s and water-soluble and corrosive salts such as [[aluminum nitride]], [[sodium chloride]] and [[potassium chloride]].  There are also around 75,000&nbsp;cu&nbsp;yd of [[salt cake]].  Groundwater is contaminated by [[arsenic]], soils are contaminated by arsenic and [[PCBs]] and a nearby creek is contaminated by [[cadmium]].  Access to the site is unrestricted, so trespassers may come into contact with contaminants.<ref>{{cite web| title=NPL Site Narrative for Smokey Mountain Smelters|url=http://www.epa.gov/superfund/sites/npl/nar1817.htm |accessdate=2010-05-05}}</ref>|| {{center|03/04/2010}} || {{center|09/29/2010<ref>http://epa.gov/region4/superfund/sites/npl/tennessee/smokmtsmtn.html</ref><ref>http://www.epa.gov/superfund/sites/query/queryhtm/nplfin.htm#TN</ref>}} || {{center|&ndash;}} || {{center|&ndash;}} || {{center|&ndash;}}
