A '''Sievert chamber''' is a type of [[ionization chamber]] used in radiation dose measurements. It was invented by Professor [[Rolf Maximilian Sievert]] in [[Sweden]] in the years 1920-40.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rolf Sievert, the man and the unit |work=Department of Oncology-Pathology |publisher=Karolinska Institutet |date=2007-02-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url=http://ki.se/ki/jsp/polopoly.jsp?l=en&d=9498&a=18510}}</ref>
